  <TEXT> 
	 <BODY> 
		<DIV1 TYPE="letter"><PB N="[1]"> 
		  <OPENER> 
			 <ADDRESS> 
				<ADDRLINE> 
				  <NAME TYPE="place">Fort <ORIG
					 REG="Armstrong">armstrong</ORIG></NAME> 
				  <DATE VALUE="1814-02-04"><ABBR EXPAN="February">Febry</ABBR> 4th
					 1814</DATE></ADDRLINE> 
				<ADDRLINE> 
				  <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="Colonel Return Jonathan">Colo.
						R. J.</ABBR> Meigs</NAME></ADDRLINE> 
			 </ADDRESS> 
			 <SALUTE>Sir</SALUTE>:</OPENER> 
		  <P>a number of Cherokees having assembled at this place who
			 <ORIG REG="appeared">appeard</ORIG> determined on an
			 <UNCLEAR>emertion</UNCLEAR> into the 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Creek</NAME> nation to form a Junction with 
			 <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="General">Genl</ABBR> Jackson </NAME>
			 in his Late tour on 
			 <NAME TYPE="place">the <UNCLEAR><ORIG
				REG="Tallapoosa">talapoosy</ORIG></UNCLEAR></NAME> I <ORIG
			 REG="viewed">viwd</ORIG> the enterprise highly <ORIG
			 REG="improper">impropper</ORIG> as being too weak to act by ourselves and 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Jacksons</NAME> situation was but imperfectly
			 known to us <ORIG REG="indeed">inded</ORIG> I had but Little hopes of Joining
			 him as I then thought his object might be different from the prevailing opinion
			 which I thought had obtained Circulation. the better to Secure his Real object.
			 My <ORIG REG="entreaties">intreaties</ORIG> were without effect nothing Could
			 Remove their Stubborn determination when I agreed to accompany them we Left
			 this on the 
			 <DATE VALUE="0000-01-23">23rd 
				<ABBR EXPAN="January">Janry</ABBR></DATE> and directed our Course
			 for the 
			 <NAME TYPE="place">Hillabees</NAME> but on our arrival at the fork of
			 the path which Leads to the 
			 <NAME TYPE="place">Hillabees</NAME> and 
			 <NAME TYPE="place">Chinabees</NAME> fort of friendly 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Creeks</NAME> on the <UNCLEAR>Choctaw
			 Coches</UNCLEAR> they Changed their <ORIG REG="Route">Rout</ORIG> to fall in
			 the Rear of 
			 <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="General">Genl</ABBR> Jackson</NAME>
			 on our arrival at the fort we found from the Relation of the 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Creeks</NAME> that 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Jackson</NAME> had on the 
			 <DATE VALUE="0000-00-22">22nd</DATE> two <ORIG
			 REG="engagements">ingagements</ORIG> with the hostile party in which a number
			 of <ORIG REG="wounded">woonded</ORIG> was <ORIG REG=" thrown upon">throne
			 uppon</ORIG> his hands which <ORIG REG="Compelled">Compeld</ORIG> him to
			 <ORIG REG="Retrograde">Retrogade</ORIG> on the 
			 <DATE VALUE="0000-00-24">24</DATE> the indians having
			 <ORIG REG="Reinforced">Reenforced</ORIG> in Considerable numbers made a
			 Vigorous attack on his Rear who in a cowardly manner Retreated and Left the
			 company of <ORIG REG="artillery">artilery</ORIG> to maintain the
			 <UNCLEAR>unqiet</UNCLEAR> Content. they However maintained their Ground and
			 eventually <PB N="[2]"> put the enemy to Rout. they have proven what a few
			 determined <ORIG RESP="disciplined">diciplined</ORIG> men can perform they have
			 <ORIG REG="clothed">cloathed</ORIG> themselves with immortal <ORIG
			 REG="honors">honours</ORIG>. &mdash; finding 
			 <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="General">Genl.</ABBR> Jackson</NAME>
			 unable with Safety to maintain his situation I had no difficulty in inducing
			 them to follow the army to the to Islands which we <ORIG
			 REG="Reached">Reachd</ORIG> the same day with 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Jackson</NAME>in there Several
			 <ORIG REG="engagements">ingagements</ORIG> the enemy have Lost 200 of them but
			 <ORIG REG="warriors">wariors</ORIG> we have to Lament the Loss of some brave
			 men 20 fell on the field and 5 have since died of their <ORIG
			 REG="wounds">woonds</ORIG>. and 55 additional <ORIG
			 REG="wounded">woonded</ORIG> many badly but none dangerous.</P> 
		  <P>The Cherokees were permitted to Return to their Respective homes on
			 the <UNCLEAR>tattered</UNCLEAR> lands to <ORIG
			 REG="Rendezvous">Rendesvous</ORIG> at this place on the 
			 <DATE VALUE="0000-00-20">20th</DATE> at which time it is hoped they
			 will Generally attend active operations will Commence about the 
			 <DATE VALUE="0000-00-25">25th</DATE> at which time it is Supposed the
			 whole army will <ORIG REG="move">moove</ORIG>. be pleased to urge 
			 <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="Captain">Capt</ABBR> Taylor</NAME>
			 to attend his Services I found on our former movements of some importance. I
			 shall <ORIG REG="endeavor">indeavour</ORIG> to Call at 
			 <NAME TYPE="place">Highawassee</NAME> before Long when I will more
			 fully detail to you our <ORIG REG="movement">moovement</ORIG>.</P> 
		  <P> 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Mayor Walker</NAME> is here and intends
			 Continuing with about 100 <ORIG REG="warriors">wariors</ORIG> 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">the Ridge</NAME>. <UNCLEAR>Three</UNCLEAR>boats
			 and the indians from that Quarter are daily expected. I have Requested him to
			 delay his Junction to the 
			 <DATE VALUE="0000-00-20">20th</DATE> 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Lowry Brown</NAME> and their men who were about
			 marching have been advised to delay also. provisions are <ORIG
			 REG="Scarce">Scearce</ORIG> and no prospect of an immediate Supply. Should
			 <PB N="[3]"> they <ORIG REG="arrive">arive</ORIG> they must depend on their
			 Guns for <ORIG REG="Subsistence">Subsistance</ORIG></P> 
		  <CLOSER> 
			 <SALUTE>accept <ORIG REG="assurances">assureances</ORIG> of My <LB>
				perfect Esteem</SALUTE> 
			 <SIGNED> 
				<NAME TYPE="person">Gideon Morgan</NAME> <LB> 
				<ABBR EXPAN="Colonel">Colo</ABBR> Cherokee forces</SIGNED> 
			 <ADDRESS> 
				<ADDRLINE> 
				  <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="Colonel">Colo</ABBR> Return 
					 <ABBR EXPAN="Jonathan">J</ABBR> Meigs</NAME></ADDRLINE> 
			 </ADDRESS></CLOSER> 
		</DIV1> 
